Image credit: Xhosa Culture.com By Andile Mngxitama Imagine if the royal family of the AmaXhosa King Mpendulo Zwelonke Sigcawu were to reject Ramaphosa’s state funeral offer and instead insist that the state fix the mess of both healthcare and education in the Eastern Cape, as the correct way of honoring the memory of a King that was neglected by the state? Remember that the King had to wait for 6 hours for an ambulance. You can just imagine how much longer ordinary persons are made to wait. The Cuban revolutionary, Fidel Castro, insisted to the very end of his life that no public place or street be named after him, as well as no monument, statue or bust be made to commemorate him. Cuba, as small as it is, features as one of the world’s top 10 in terms of healthcare and education. Let’s get our priorities right… Andile Mngxitama is the President of the radical black consciousness organization, Black First Land First (BLF). No related posts.